    "body": "### Problem\n\n`autocomplete` option with `autocompletedelay` option set to a number higher than `0` causes actual delay when `TextChangedP` autocmd is fired and at the same time `CursorMovedI` or `TextChangedI` events don't run either.\nIt is a breaking change that prevent the user correctly detect cursor movement/ text changes in insert mode.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`nvim -u init.lua` with this `init.lua`. Then write two the same words, like \"hello hello\". The second word till menu is shown will not print anything to the cmdline.\n```lua\nvim.o.completeopt = \"menu,menuone,noselect\"\nvim.o.complete = \".,w,b,o\"\nvim.o.autocomplete = true\nvim.o.autocompletedelay = 2000\nvim.o.showmode = false\n\nlocal group = vim.api.nvim_create_augroup(\"Testing\", {})\n\nvim.api.nvim_create_autocmd({ \"CursorMovedI\", \"TextChangedI\", \"TextChangedP\", \"CompleteChanged\" }, {\n   group = group,\n   callback = function(ev)\n      local pos = vim.api.nvim_win_get_cursor(0)\n      vim.print(vim.api.nvim_buf_get_text(ev.buf, pos[1] - 1, pos[2] - 1, pos[1] - 1, pos[2], {})[1])\n   end\n})\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSome autocmd should be triggered, so cursor movement or text changes can be detected in insert mode.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.13 nightly\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nHave not tested\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nfoot\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nfoot\n\n### Installation\n\nAUR (neovim-nightly-bin)",
